e OpenCode runtime when:. * You are building a UI on top of an OpenCode agent server. If your backend is not OpenCode-based, see picking a runtime for alternatives. `@assistant-ui/react-opencode` is layered on `ExternalStoreRuntime` plus a `RemoteThreadList` for session-backed thread management (see architecture). OpenCode sessions map to assistant-ui threads; the runtime subscribes to a server-sent event stream and projects messages into the thread. npm install @assistant-ui/react @assistant-ui/react-opencode @opencode-ai/sdk. QuickstartMinimal useOpenCodeRuntime setup against a local OpenCode server.HooksPermissions, questions, session state, runtime extras.", "score": 0.57064295, "raw_content": "[![assistant-ui logo](/favicon/icon.svg)assistant-ui](/)/[Docs](/docs)/Runtimes\n\nOpenCode\n\n# OpenCode Runtime\n\nBuild a React chat UI for OpenCode coding agents with assistant-ui — streaming, tool calls, file edits, and terminal output rendered in chat.\n\n`@assistant-ui/react-opencode` is a runtime adapter for [OpenCode](https://opencode.ai/), an open-source AI coding agent. It wires the OpenCode server's session and event APIs into an assistant-ui thread, including tool permissions, interactive questions, and session state.\n\nThis adapter is at v0.0.3 and is experimental. The runtime API and exported hooks may change without notice.\n\n## [When to use it](#when-to-use-it)\n\nPick the OpenCode runtime when:\n\n* You are building a UI on top of an OpenCode agent server.\n* You need first-class support for OpenCode's permission and question flows.\n* You want session-aware features: fork, revert, unrevert, refresh.\n\nIf your backend is not OpenCode-based, see [picking a runtime](/docs/runtimes/pick-a-runtime) for alternatives.\n\n## [Architecture](#architecture)\n\n`@assistant-ui/react-opencode` is layered on `ExternalStoreRuntime` plus a `RemoteThreadList` for session-backed thread management (see [architecture](/docs/runtimes/concepts/architecture)). OpenCode sessions map to assistant-ui threads; the runtime subscribes to a server-sent event stream and projects messages into the thread.\n\n## [Requirements](#requirements)\n\n* A running [OpenCode](https://opencode.ai/) server (defaults to `http://localhost:4096`).\n* React 18 or 19.\n\n## [Install](#install)\n\n```\nnpm install @assistant-ui/react @assistant-ui/react-opencode @opencode-ai/sdk\n```\n\n## [Next](#next)\n\n[QuickstartMinimal useOpenCodeRuntime setup against a local OpenCode server.](/docs/runtimes/opencode/quickstart)[HooksPermissions, questions, session state, runtime extras.](/docs/runtimes/opencode/hooks)\n\nOn this page\n\n* [When to use it](#when-to-use-it)\n* [Architecture](#architecture)\n* [Requirements](#requirements)\n* [Install](#install)\n* [Next](#next)\n\n[View as Markdown](https://www.assistant-ui.com/docs/runtimes/opencode/overview.mdx)[Edit on GitHub](https://github.com/assistant-ui/assistant-ui/edit/main/apps/docs/content/docs/runtimes/opencode/overview.mdx)\n\n[We are hiring\n\nBuild the future of agentic UI with us →](/careers)"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/@gaharwar.milind/inside-opencode-how-to-build-an-ai-coding-agent-that-actually-works-28c614494f4f", "title": "Inside OpenCode: How to Build an AI Coding Agent That Actually ...", "content": "A deep dive into the architecture of OpenCode, the open-source AI coding assistant that's changing how developers work.", "score": 0.4800161, "raw_content": null}], "response_time": 1.91, "request_id": "8bc75f09-e579-4691-993d-b6ae06341c9d"}